</td></tr><tr><td width=10% Bgcolor=#101010 Align=center Valign=top><table width=200><tr><td align=center><font size=-1><table><tr><td align=center><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_top.jpg><br clear=all><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_left.jpg><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/portraits/RENALINI.jpg width="104" height="184"><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_right.jpg><br clear=all><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_bottom.jpg></td></tr></table>Legendary  RENALINI<br>Level 62 Cleric<br><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_7.gif" title="Star of Achievement"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_11.gif" title="Silver Order of Leadership"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_1.gif" title="Service Cross"><br>Knight<br><a style="text-decoration:none;" href="main.cgi?fetch=RENALINI"><font size=-1 color="#DDDDDD">RENALINI</font></a><font size=-1>'S LINEAGE</font><br><img src='http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/bio.gif' border=0></font></td></tr></table></td><td width=90% Valign=top><a href=main.cgi?followup=2&forum=9><p align=right><font color=#cccccc>Reply | </a><a href=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/guild-builder/call/main.cgi?action=messages&forum=9><font color=#cccccc>Return</a></p><br clear=all><p><i>I've done some testing after seeing posts at other forums that spoke to exactly what /pause does.<br><br>Contrary to the information SOE released, a pause of 1 is NOT 1/10th of a second. A pause of 10 is NOT 1 second.<br><br>Repeated tests I ran earlier showed that I consistently got a 10 second differential by using a pause of 75.<br><br>I tested this by sitting in PoK in a place where I was getting no lag or framerate lag and clicking off a hotkey.<br><br>The hotkey is this:<br><br>/time<br>/pause 75<br>/time<br>/pause 75<br>/time<br><br>Since /time does not report in milliseconds, I can only be reasonably sure that /pause 75 is CLOSE to a ten second pause, meaning that 1 second = /pause 7.5. I am probably off by a little bit, but no more than 1 or 2 tenths of a second.<br><br>Please feel free to test this yourselves and post your results.<br><br>edit: Tested against a different computer, more powerful than the one I used this morning. /pause 75 comes out to 8.5 to 9 seconds on this machine. So it looks like it might be machine dependant.<br clear=all><br><font size=-2>(Edited by RENALINI on 7/31/2003 at 8:43p.m.)</font><br><font size=-2>(Edited by RENALINI on 7/31/2003 at 11:45a.m.)</font><br></i><br></td></tr><tr><td>
